modules.description: This module handles Htmx-specific interactions by inspecting incoming requests and modifying responses to control client-side behavior. It works with HTTP requests and responses, extracting Htmx metadata like triggers, targets, and prompts, and injecting Htmx commands such as redirects, refreshes, and event triggers. Use it to implement dynamic UI updates, form submissions, and client navigation in Htmx-powered web applications.
